window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>In this stunning sequel to </b><b><i>The Hundred Thousand Kingdoms</i></b><b>, one blind woman will challenge the will of the gods and change the fate of the world.</b></p> <p>In the city of Shadow, beneath the World Tree, alleyways shimmer with magic and godlings live hidden among mortalkind. Oree Shoth, a blind artist, takes in a strange homeless man on an impulse. This act of kindness engulfs Oree in a nightmarish conspiracy. Someone, somehow, is murdering godlings, leaving their desecrated bodies all over the city. And Oree's guest is at the heart of it....</p> <p><b>The Inheritance Trilogy </b></p> <p></p> <ul> <li><i>The Hundred Thousand Kingdoms</i></li> <li><i>The Broken Kingdoms</i></li> <li><i>The Kingdom of Gods</i></li> <li><i>The Inheritance Trilogy </i>(omnibus edition)&nbsp;</li> <li><i>Shades in Shadow: An Inheritance Triptych</i> (e-only short fiction)&nbsp;</li> <li><i>The Awakened Kingdom </i>(e-only novella)&nbsp;</li> </ul> <p>For more from N. K. Jemisin, check out:</p> <p><b>Dreamblood Duology</b></p> <p></p> <ul> <li><i>The Killing Moon</i></li> <li><i>The Shadowed Sun</i>&nbsp;</li> </ul> <p><b>The Broken Earth series </b></p> <p></p> <ul> <li><i>The Fifth Season</i></li> <li><i>The Obelisk Gate</i></li> <li><i>The Stone Sky</i></li> </ul>"; 
